Headlines.Author: Tess Stynes
Headlines.Headline: Fossil Group Profit Fell 1.7% on Higher Expenses

PARAGRAPH.#text: Fossil Group Inc. FOSL said fourth-quarter earnings fell 1.7% as the fashion-accessories retailer's sales growth was offset by higher expenses. Shares rose 4.9% to $122.65 in recent after-hours trading as results beat expectations. However, for the current quarter, Fossil forecast per-share earnings below expectations of $1.10 to $1.18 on sales growth of 12.5% to 14%. Analysts polled by Thomson Reuters had expected per-share profit of $1.30 and revenue growth of 11% to $758 million. For 2014, the company forecast per-share earnings of $6.90 to $7.30 on sales growth of 8% to 10%.

Headlines.Author: Billy Crosby
Headlines.Headline: Fossil 2nd-Quarter Earnings Up 18%; Increases Year Guidance

PARAGRAPH.#text: Fossil Inc.'s FOSL second-quarter earnings jumped 18% as the fashion-accessories retailer reported sales increases in all segments. The company raised its full-year earnings guidance, now projecting $6.15 to $6.35 a share, from its May estimate of $6 to $6.26 a share. It now expects net sales to increase between 11% and 12%, up from 10% to 11% growth. The company estimated current-quarter earnings at $1.30 to $1.37 a share on 12.5% to 13.5% sales growth, above the view of analysts surveyed by Thomson Reuters who expect $1.46 a share in earnings on an 11% sales increase.
